<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-2860] camel-ftp - Should use absolute paths, eg the leading / should always be included</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-2860</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;FTP Servers expect clients to use absolute paths, so camel-ftp clients should not clip any leading /&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We could consider adding a flag to preserve the old behavior to have people if they rely on the old behavior be able to switch that flag on.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12486260">CAMEL-2860</key>
